### Phase 1: Research & Inspiration

1. **Gather References**: Browse Dribbble, Behance, Pinterest
2. **Bookmark Favorites**: Save inspiring designs
3. **Analyze Patterns**: Note what makes designs effective
4. **Document Insights**: Create visual mood boards

### Phase 2: Style Rule Creation

1. **Define Color Palette**:

   ```css
   --primary: #your-brand-color;
   --secondary: #supporting-color;
   --neutral-900: #background-dark;
   --neutral-100: #background-light;
   --text-primary: #high-contrast-text;
   --text-secondary: #medium-contrast-text;
   ```

2. **Establish Spacing Scale**:

   ```css
   --space-1: 0.25rem;  /* 4px */
   --space-2: 0.5rem;   /* 8px */
   --space-3: 0.75rem;  /* 12px */
   --space-4: 1rem;     /* 16px */
   --space-6: 1.5rem;   /* 24px */
   --space-8: 2rem;     /* 32px */
   --space-12: 3rem;    /* 48px */
   ```

3. **Typography Scale**:

   ```css
   --text-xs: 0.75rem;   /* 12px */
   --text-sm: 0.875rem;  /* 14px */
   --text-base: 1rem;    /* 16px */
   --text-lg: 1.125rem;  /* 18px */
   --text-xl: 1.25rem;   /* 20px */
   --text-2xl: 1.5rem;   /* 24px */
   --text-3xl: 1.875rem; /* 30px */
   ```

4. **Component Standards**:
   - Buttons: Consistent padding, radius, hover states
   - Cards: Standard shadows/borders, spacing
   - Forms: Uniform input styling, validation states
   - Navigation: Consistent active/inactive states

